WEBVTT

00:06.047 --> 00:06.756
MAYNARD BARNES:
You got three options.

00:07.214 --> 00:09.005
Plead Emily Dodson out,
tank the case in trial,

00:09.089 --> 00:11.673
or get yourself disbarred.

00:12.172 --> 00:13.214
E.B. JONATHON:
There's no way you'd be

00:13.422 --> 00:16.088
dredging up old ghosts
if you had a solid case!

00:16.172 --> 00:17.255
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

00:17.589 --> 00:20.172
MAN: The ramifications
of Sister's latest message

00:20.422 --> 00:23.422
threatens the financial health
of the assembly.

00:24.381 --> 00:25.422
WOMAN:
Half of your audience wanna

00:25.714 --> 00:27.756
kiss your feet,
the other half wanna kill you.

00:28.798 --> 00:30.255
You have to let me protect you.

00:30.756 --> 00:33.255
Charlie Dodson will rise again!

00:33.798 --> 00:35.255
Blasphemy!

00:35.339 --> 00:36.506
PETE STRICKLAND:
Three guys, three stiffs.

00:36.589 --> 00:38.047
'Cept we know there's a fourth.

00:38.130 --> 00:40.172
You're like every amateur dick
I ever met.

00:40.255 --> 00:41.172
You think you caught a fish

00:41.255 --> 00:42.673
all you done is
hook your own ass.

00:42.756 --> 00:44.172
E.B. JONATHON:
Mr. Mason's evidence

00:44.255 --> 00:45.255
is coming up short.

00:46.089 --> 00:48.255
You want me to say
that I'm guilty?

00:48.339 --> 00:49.339
No, we're gonna fight.

00:49.631 --> 00:50.589
I'm the lawyer here!

00:50.673 --> 00:52.756
Then act like one goddammit!

00:55.964 --> 00:57.631
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

01:04.631 --> 01:06.130
(DOORBELL RINGS)

01:16.297 --> 01:17.798
(DOORBELL RINGS)

01:29.172 --> 01:30.214
E.B.?

01:37.005 --> 01:40.839
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

01:55.589 --> 01:57.005
(GAS STOVE HISSING)

01:57.089 --> 01:58.506
(GASPS)

02:00.923 --> 02:02.047
(CHOKING)

02:12.547 --> 02:13.923
(HISSING STOPS)

02:18.255 --> 02:19.339
E.B.?

02:19.422 --> 02:20.422
E.B.?

02:21.464 --> 02:22.506
E.B.?

02:23.172 --> 02:24.339
E.B.?

02:24.422 --> 02:26.714
E.B.? E.B.?

02:30.631 --> 02:32.547
(SOBBING)

02:38.089 --> 02:40.089
(CRIES) No.

02:42.714 --> 02:46.214
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

02:59.589 --> 03:01.714
Boyle 23405...

03:03.756 --> 03:08.214
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

03:11.506 --> 03:13.047
(SOBBING)

04:02.047 --> 04:03.547
DELLA STREET: It's funny,

04:03.631 --> 04:07.255
you spend all these years
with somebody, and...

04:08.130 --> 04:10.464
one day,
they're just gone.

04:11.422 --> 04:12.923
And you realize...

04:15.881 --> 04:17.673
you'll never see them again.

04:20.464 --> 04:23.297
But I guess that's life,
isn't it?

04:27.506 --> 04:32.589
So first you found him dead,
and then you called the police?

04:32.673 --> 04:34.339
Yes.

04:34.422 --> 04:36.464
That's exactly what I did.

04:39.172 --> 04:41.089
I can assure you that all of us

04:41.172 --> 04:44.089
at Century Mutual
are sorry for your loss.

04:44.172 --> 04:46.130
May I ask if you need
any assistance

04:46.214 --> 04:47.464
with funeral arrangements?

04:47.547 --> 04:50.839
-We have relationships with--
-Thank you. No.

04:50.923 --> 04:54.923
The body is being taken
to be with his family.

04:55.005 --> 04:56.339
Up north.

04:56.422 --> 05:01.506
PORTER:
Next stops be Atascadero,
Salinas, Watsonville Junction,

05:01.589 --> 05:05.464
South San Francisco,
San Francisco.

05:05.547 --> 05:09.214
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

05:31.130 --> 05:32.714
Not much longer now.

05:35.130 --> 05:40.255
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

05:56.798 --> 06:00.214
♪ (MUSIC CONTINUES) ♪

06:16.089 --> 06:17.422
Mother?

06:19.381 --> 06:21.297
Can I have 25,000 dollars?

06:21.381 --> 06:22.798
Twenty-five thousand dollars?

06:22.881 --> 06:24.297
SISTER ALICE MCKEEGAN:
For Emily Dodson.

06:24.381 --> 06:26.214
That is the amount
of her bail, isn't it?

06:26.297 --> 06:29.839
Are you-- Are you
suggesting we-- we free her?

06:29.923 --> 06:32.631
I want Emily sitting
on stage with me.

06:32.714 --> 06:34.214
She can take Elder Brown's seat.

06:34.297 --> 06:36.464
That's not the wisest path
to tread at this moment, Sister.

06:36.547 --> 06:38.130
SISTER ALICE: Look at these!

06:38.214 --> 06:42.089
This outpouring of love
and charity.

06:42.172 --> 06:45.130
Chesterfield, Missouri,
two dollars.

06:46.631 --> 06:51.381
Bangor, Maine,
five dollars and...

06:51.464 --> 06:55.255
forty-three-- 46 cents.

06:55.339 --> 06:56.964
Tucson, Arizona.

06:58.047 --> 07:00.214
"May God pour honey
over your body

07:00.297 --> 07:03.464
and stake you to an ant hill,
you blaspheming whore.

07:03.547 --> 07:06.297
You couldn't die soon enough."

07:06.381 --> 07:08.839
Elder Seidel, how much
did we bring in this week?

07:08.923 --> 07:11.172
ELDER SEIDEL: Uh, enough
to cover our overhead

07:11.964 --> 07:13.130
and to keep the kitchen stocked.

07:13.214 --> 07:14.756
SISTER ALICE:
And it will be double that

07:14.839 --> 07:16.422
when I return
to the microphone.

07:16.506 --> 07:18.881
Never in my life
have I felt stronger

07:18.964 --> 07:24.547
or more clear in my mind
or more filled with inspiration.

07:26.339 --> 07:27.631
I think it's been some time

07:27.714 --> 07:30.214
since we've had
a divine healing.

07:30.297 --> 07:32.381
Well, it's hard to capture
the true spirit

07:32.464 --> 07:34.547
of that particular service
on the radio, Sister.

07:34.631 --> 07:37.172
The gospel will reach out
through that radio

07:37.255 --> 07:41.506
and around the world to every
man, woman, boy and girl.

07:41.589 --> 07:46.506
As the hymns say, "To answer
when He calls, that is my task."

07:51.089 --> 07:54.839
(SIGHS) You can come down
off your chariot.

07:55.923 --> 07:57.506
We're paying attention.

08:00.547 --> 08:03.673
Bring me the weak and the sick
like we did under tent poles

08:03.756 --> 08:05.381
before we broke ground.

08:05.464 --> 08:07.464
And if you cannot
accommodate that, Mother,

08:07.547 --> 08:09.714
then you can be relieved
of your duties.

08:12.673 --> 08:14.214
Anything else, daughter?

08:15.381 --> 08:17.381
Just 25,000 dollars.

08:27.214 --> 08:29.005
PETE STRICKLAND:
Look, Detective,

08:29.089 --> 08:31.047
I already been tailing Ennis
for three days.

08:31.130 --> 08:33.547
I'm asking who might have a beef
with this prick.

08:33.631 --> 08:36.005
And guess whose name
keeps popping up? Yours.

08:36.089 --> 08:37.839
-RAY ROYCE: Hey, Flint.
-Yeah?

08:37.923 --> 08:40.798
Get your nose out of her pills
and go burn some coffee.

08:40.881 --> 08:42.422
Fucking reeks in here.

08:45.547 --> 08:47.255
You believe this shit?

08:48.798 --> 08:50.673
What got at her face?

08:50.756 --> 08:52.381
Goddamn cat.

08:53.422 --> 08:55.923
Ugh.
Ate her whole fucking ear off.

08:57.464 --> 09:00.589
Look, I'm on the Dodson case.
Things ain't adding up.

09:01.339 --> 09:02.464
This guy, Joe Ennis,

09:02.547 --> 09:04.839
he seems to be sitting
in the shadow of most of them.

09:04.923 --> 09:08.297
I was first up
the day little Charlie came in.

09:08.381 --> 09:09.673
It was my case.

09:09.756 --> 09:11.839
That prick Ennis
paid the division chief

09:11.923 --> 09:14.172
to jump in front of me.
My fucking case.

09:14.255 --> 09:15.923
Biggest case in town.

09:16.005 --> 09:17.130
FLINT: Hey, Sarge?

09:17.214 --> 09:20.130
I found the kitty-cat.
It's dead too.

09:21.089 --> 09:23.506
I hope it choked on her earring.

09:23.589 --> 09:27.422
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

09:27.506 --> 09:29.923
(CHILDREN CHATTER)

09:51.631 --> 09:52.839
BYRON JONATHAN:
Miss Street?

09:52.923 --> 09:56.005
Yes. Hello, Mr. Jonathan.

09:56.089 --> 09:58.589
Let me express
our deepest sympathies

09:58.673 --> 10:00.923
to you and your family
in this time of--

10:01.005 --> 10:02.881
Thank you.
You must be Mr. Mason.

10:02.964 --> 10:04.756
It's Byron, isn't it?

10:04.839 --> 10:07.255
BYRON: I'd like to thank you
both for coming all this way.

10:07.339 --> 10:09.589
-It really wasn't necessary.
-Of course it was.

10:09.673 --> 10:11.964
BYRON: Whatever it cost you,
please send me a bill.

10:12.047 --> 10:14.673
You shouldn't be out of pocket.

10:14.756 --> 10:17.798
Well, the trunk has some
of his things from the house.

10:17.881 --> 10:19.756
There's still a lot
to go through, I'm afraid.

10:19.839 --> 10:21.547
Please don't trouble
yourself any further.

10:21.631 --> 10:24.464
I'll see that it all gets
taken to a consignment shop.

10:26.172 --> 10:28.255
Byron, I-- I'm sorry,
I have to ask.

10:28.339 --> 10:31.172
I mean, what-- where...
where is everybody?

10:32.047 --> 10:33.964
Your wife? The grandkids?

10:34.047 --> 10:36.214
BYRON:
At home. At school.

10:36.297 --> 10:39.756
You-- You're telling me
he actually mentioned my kids?

10:39.839 --> 10:41.589
He-- He had pictures of them.

10:41.673 --> 10:44.964
But did he ever talk
about them or about me,

10:45.047 --> 10:46.464
about my sister?

10:46.547 --> 10:47.923
Did he ever mention
my mother,

10:48.005 --> 10:49.381
who's inside there with him?

10:49.464 --> 10:51.214
PERRY MASON:
Well, it doesn't--

10:51.297 --> 10:53.839
it doesn't mean you weren't
in his thoughts

10:53.923 --> 10:56.673
or-- or that he didn't care.

10:57.673 --> 11:00.089
He was a very private man.

11:00.172 --> 11:01.130
BYRON: Yes.

11:01.214 --> 11:03.589
Well, we didn't talk
about him either.

11:03.673 --> 11:05.589
And, to be honest,
I don't care.

11:07.381 --> 11:08.923
DELLA: The check
from his life insurance

11:09.005 --> 11:10.673
will be mailed directly to you.

11:10.756 --> 11:14.130
I'll see that his will is
probated as soon as we get back.

11:14.214 --> 11:16.673
Will you be needing a ride back
to the train or to a hotel?

11:16.756 --> 11:18.089
MASON: No. Thank you.

11:23.381 --> 11:24.756
DELLA: That was warm.

11:27.714 --> 11:30.547
MASON: It wasn't right, Della.

11:31.923 --> 11:34.005
It wasn't right.

11:34.089 --> 11:36.339
He knew you'd be there
in the morning.

11:36.422 --> 11:40.881
He knew you'd--
you'd find him and...

11:41.798 --> 11:43.756
Arrange things?

11:45.923 --> 11:48.422
I suppose I should thank you.

11:48.506 --> 11:50.756
For what?
Helping turn his suicide

11:50.839 --> 11:54.506
into a more insurance-friendly
demise?

11:54.589 --> 11:55.964
Forget it.

11:57.339 --> 12:00.089
It's very easy for you
to break the rules, isn't it?

12:00.172 --> 12:04.172
Well, the way I see it,
there's what's legal

12:04.255 --> 12:05.839
and there's what's right.

12:07.839 --> 12:11.464
You know, you can be
profoundly irritating.

12:11.547 --> 12:13.881
-All right.
-DELLA: You drink too much.

12:13.964 --> 12:17.005
Your personal habits leave
a lot to be desired.

12:17.089 --> 12:19.798
And quite frankly,
I find it offensive

12:19.881 --> 12:23.506
that you choose to mask
your intelligence and decency

12:23.589 --> 12:26.297
with cynicism and slothfulness.

12:26.923 --> 12:28.297
Is that all?

12:29.297 --> 12:32.089
And you never accept any help.

12:32.172 --> 12:35.130
I'm letting you help me
finish this bottle.

12:41.506 --> 12:44.297
You come from money, don't you?

12:45.297 --> 12:47.839
Why do you say that?

12:47.923 --> 12:49.881
-The way you sit.
-(CHUCKLES)

12:49.964 --> 12:52.172
-Just little things.
-Mm-hmm?

12:52.255 --> 12:56.464
Your subtle
and not-so-subtle judgments.

12:59.673 --> 13:02.673
I ran away from home
when I was 25.

13:04.255 --> 13:06.381
Goodbye, arranged fiancé.

13:07.172 --> 13:09.130
Goodbye...

13:09.214 --> 13:11.547
father who wouldn't let me go
to college.

13:12.172 --> 13:14.089
Goodbye, inheritance.

13:14.172 --> 13:17.923
Hello, E.B. Jonathan
and Associates.

13:18.005 --> 13:20.547
Answered a classified
in the Examiner,

13:20.631 --> 13:22.631
"Busy downtown firm
seeks secretary."

13:22.714 --> 13:23.923
I showed up.

13:24.005 --> 13:27.839
It was just the two of them
sitting behind their desks,

13:28.381 --> 13:32.714
Lyle and... E.B.

13:33.381 --> 13:35.130
I mean, Lyle's a shark,

13:35.214 --> 13:37.339
-but E.B. was...
-DELLA: Vain?

13:37.422 --> 13:39.381
Short-tempered?

13:39.964 --> 13:41.547
Self-absorbed?

13:41.631 --> 13:44.130
MASON: He was living a lie.

13:44.214 --> 13:46.381
Do you think
that's why he did it?

13:48.214 --> 13:49.589
(SIGHS)

13:55.297 --> 13:57.047
Does it not even matter anymore?

13:57.130 --> 14:00.464
MASON: Well,
I think it mattered to E.B.

14:00.547 --> 14:03.631
I think that's why
he chose his own terms.

14:03.714 --> 14:06.172
Wrote his own epitaph.

14:06.255 --> 14:12.589
"Here lies E.B. Jonathan,
defender of all the innocent,

14:12.673 --> 14:16.255
righter of wrongs,
all-around good guy."

14:17.297 --> 14:19.381
Unless you're talking
to his son.

14:23.756 --> 14:26.756
Here's to all the shitty fathers
in the world.

14:29.714 --> 14:33.923
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

14:44.089 --> 14:46.214
DELLA:
Can you ring room 18?

14:46.297 --> 14:47.255
Perry Mason.

14:47.339 --> 14:49.964
Mr. Mason checked out
an hour ago, ma'am.

14:53.214 --> 14:54.422
Thank you.

14:56.923 --> 15:01.130
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

15:29.464 --> 15:30.839
MASON: Thank you.

15:37.839 --> 15:41.172
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

15:47.339 --> 15:48.798
(KNOCKS)

15:58.339 --> 15:59.547
MASON: Hi, Cheryl.

16:00.839 --> 16:02.381
It's good to see you.

16:04.631 --> 16:06.506
-Linda here--
-CHERYL ANDERSON: Linda?

16:06.589 --> 16:08.255
-LINDA: Yeah?
-Door.

16:19.714 --> 16:21.297
What are you doing here?

16:21.381 --> 16:23.964
Well, I was-- I was working
a case in the area,

16:24.047 --> 16:25.255
so I thought...

16:28.089 --> 16:30.089
You look terrible.
Are you drunk?

16:30.172 --> 16:31.964
-Probably.
-LINDA: Jesus, Perry.

16:32.047 --> 16:34.297
You can't show up here drunk.

16:34.381 --> 16:36.297
E.B. is dead, Lin.

16:36.381 --> 16:39.547
He-- He died. He's-- He's dead.

16:46.339 --> 16:47.589
I'm sorry.

16:49.255 --> 16:51.422
I know when your dad
passed, E.B. was--

16:51.506 --> 16:53.589
I'm not-- I'm not looking
for a hug or anything.

16:53.673 --> 16:58.881
I just-- I just wanted to spend
some time with my son.

17:00.923 --> 17:02.631
He's out back playing.

17:03.255 --> 17:04.547
Thank you.

17:05.589 --> 17:07.255
LINDA: Wait.

17:07.339 --> 17:10.089
You think you wanna come inside
and clean up a bit?

17:10.798 --> 17:12.047
I'm fine.

17:15.047 --> 17:16.756
♪ (SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

17:25.923 --> 17:27.214
TEDDY MASON: Daddy. Daddy!

17:30.089 --> 17:33.422
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

17:45.214 --> 17:47.297
Why in God's name
is she in chains?

17:47.381 --> 17:49.047
DETECTIVE ENNIS:
Standard procedure, ma'am.

17:49.130 --> 17:52.339
Standard should include
a certain level of decency.

17:52.422 --> 17:54.381
I'm sure you're right
about that, ma'am.

17:54.464 --> 17:56.214
SISTER ALICE: Do you want
something to eat, Emily?

17:56.297 --> 17:58.547
-EMILY DODSON: Mm-hmm.
-Maybe hot bath?

17:58.631 --> 18:00.297
DETECTIVE HOLCOMB:
That's Alice McKeegan,

18:00.381 --> 18:01.798
-you are Birdy McKeegan.
-Yes and yes.

18:01.881 --> 18:03.798
And you agree to serve
as Emily Dodson's custodians

18:03.881 --> 18:05.422
-after posting bail?
-Yes.

18:05.506 --> 18:07.923
HOLCOMB: Number one,
Mrs. Dodson is to remain

18:08.005 --> 18:09.756
confined on these premises
from dusk to dawn,

18:09.839 --> 18:11.589
-unless otherwise directed
by the court.
-Yes.

18:11.673 --> 18:13.339
HOLCOMB: Number two,
these premises are subject

18:13.422 --> 18:15.047
-to search at any time.
-BIRDY MCKEEGAN: Yes.

18:15.130 --> 18:16.839
HOLCOMB: Number three,
Mrs. Dodson's not allowed

18:16.923 --> 18:18.297
to leave the state
of California.

18:18.381 --> 18:19.381
Yes.

18:22.923 --> 18:25.422
(SIGHS)

18:25.506 --> 18:27.339
-It's soft.
-It's mine.

18:27.422 --> 18:30.506
I had it moved in when I knew
you were coming to stay with us.

18:30.589 --> 18:33.422
You shouldn't have.
I don't need much.

18:33.506 --> 18:36.297
SISTER ALICE: Really, I sleep
standing up half the time.

18:36.381 --> 18:37.464
Go on.

18:44.798 --> 18:48.506
You're here for a reason.
You and me both.

18:51.214 --> 18:53.047
Sister, what you said--

18:56.047 --> 18:57.339
what you said about Charlie...

18:57.422 --> 18:58.923
SISTER ALICE:
We've been called, Emily,

18:59.005 --> 19:05.130
to be free of self
and filled with the Holy Spirit,

19:05.214 --> 19:10.214
to be led by the Holy Spirit,
to see each other saved.

19:11.172 --> 19:13.506
Can I be saved, Sister?

19:14.714 --> 19:16.047
Can I?

19:26.214 --> 19:29.214
-Those curtains are new.
-Yeah.

19:29.297 --> 19:33.297
-MASON: They're nice.
-Thank you.

19:33.381 --> 19:35.297
It's very kind of you
to notice.

19:40.047 --> 19:43.589
-Do you want more coffee?
-Thanks.

19:47.255 --> 19:49.172
So what time does Ed roll in?

19:49.255 --> 19:51.005
He must be putting in
some serious hours

19:51.089 --> 19:52.339
down at Spreckel.

19:52.422 --> 19:54.673
Does dinner wait on him
or do you put

19:54.756 --> 19:56.881
a plate in the oven for later?

19:56.964 --> 20:00.130
Cher, do you mind seeing
if, uh,

20:00.214 --> 20:01.923
Teddy needs help
with his homework?

20:07.589 --> 20:08.964
He doing well in school?

20:11.923 --> 20:13.923
You're not staying for dinner.

20:16.631 --> 20:18.881
Now, I don't know what this is,
this--

20:18.964 --> 20:20.673
this thing you're working on.

20:20.756 --> 20:23.798
You just drop by
out of the blue sky.

20:25.631 --> 20:28.422
You're supposed
to send the checks.

20:28.506 --> 20:32.923
You don't. Birthdays,
Christmas, you screw that up.

20:33.005 --> 20:36.631
And now you just show up here
and you-- (SNIFFLES)

20:38.339 --> 20:40.214
Do you know
what that does to Teddy?

20:40.297 --> 20:42.464
Well, I was thinking
maybe he could come

20:42.547 --> 20:44.631
spend some time with me
on the farm.

20:47.172 --> 20:48.798
It's hardly a farm.

20:50.547 --> 20:53.881
Well, then why'd you tell him
I'm a fucking farmer?

20:53.964 --> 20:57.089
Because I don't know
what to tell him you are.

20:57.172 --> 20:59.255
Poking around
people's dirty linens,

20:59.339 --> 21:01.422
hanging out at the morgue,

21:01.506 --> 21:04.255
getting your nose
knocked in twice a week.

21:04.339 --> 21:06.130
You're supposed to be
his father.

21:06.214 --> 21:07.422
I am his father.

21:07.506 --> 21:10.047
No, Perry, you are not.

21:14.464 --> 21:16.005
That ship has sailed.

