37:48.089 --> 37:51.255
(CROWD CHEERING)

37:51.339 --> 37:54.172
And there came a sound
from heaven,

37:54.255 --> 37:59.464
a sound that The Good Book says
came like a mighty wind.

37:59.547 --> 38:02.964
And it was this wind
that filled the house

38:03.047 --> 38:04.547
where they were sitting.

38:04.631 --> 38:07.547
There you are, brother.
Yes. Yes, come.

38:09.798 --> 38:11.255
You don't need that chair.

38:11.339 --> 38:17.381
And there appeared before them
cloven tongues made of fire.

38:17.464 --> 38:20.506
And what happened next?
Who can tell me?

38:20.589 --> 38:21.964
WOMAN: The Holy Spirit.

38:22.047 --> 38:24.255
Yes. Yes, brothers and sisters.

38:24.339 --> 38:28.422
Their lungs were flooded
with the Holy Ghost.

38:28.506 --> 38:31.798
And they began to speak
in different tongues,

38:31.881 --> 38:34.464
as the Spirit
gave them utterance.

38:34.547 --> 38:36.297
That chair's an excuse.

38:36.381 --> 38:38.881
And it was quite a party

38:38.964 --> 38:42.005
because there were all sorts
of people there.

38:42.089 --> 38:44.714
Jews, Romans,

38:44.798 --> 38:49.047
Arabians,
Elamites, Mesopotamians.

38:49.130 --> 38:52.964
But... (SHUSHING)

38:53.047 --> 38:59.005
But everyone could understand
everyone else because now,

38:59.089 --> 39:03.172
now they were speaking
in divine tongues,

39:03.255 --> 39:05.756
the works of God.

39:05.839 --> 39:08.381
(CROWD CHEERING)

39:08.464 --> 39:12.172
Get up. He's got your legs.
Where's your faith?

39:12.255 --> 39:15.506
-What's your name, Brother?
-It's Robert.

39:15.589 --> 39:17.589
SISTER ALICE: Get up, Robert.

39:17.673 --> 39:22.506
You don't need that chair
if you have faith, Robert.

39:22.589 --> 39:27.089
You don't need that chair
if you feel the fire of Christ

39:27.172 --> 39:29.089
inside you, Robert.

39:29.172 --> 39:31.881
-Can you feel it?
-I feel it.

39:31.964 --> 39:36.130
SISTER ALICE: You do feel it?
Yes. He feels it.

39:36.214 --> 39:39.005
The age of miracles
is here again.

39:39.089 --> 39:42.339
What was truth in the Bible
is truth again.

39:42.422 --> 39:47.339
(SPEAKING IN TONGUES)

39:54.673 --> 39:58.339
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

39:59.589 --> 40:01.798
(SPEAKING IN TONGUES)

40:07.130 --> 40:08.506
(SCREAMS)

40:10.464 --> 40:14.673
(CROWD CHEERING)

40:17.130 --> 40:19.798
♪ (CHOIR SINGING) ♪

40:40.464 --> 40:42.089
Do you believe in miracles?

40:42.172 --> 40:43.214
MAN: We believe!

40:43.297 --> 40:44.798
SISTER ALICE: I can't hear you!

40:45.547 --> 40:49.255
Yes, yes, yes.
Yes, I believe.

40:49.339 --> 40:50.964
SISTER ALICE:
Do you believe?

40:51.422 --> 40:52.798
Do you believe?

40:54.089 --> 40:57.756
Yes! Yes, Robert.

40:57.839 --> 41:03.923
Look how strong you are, Robert.
Look at you. Beautiful, Robert.

41:04.005 --> 41:05.589
Yes. Yes.

41:05.673 --> 41:08.881
You can do it, oh,
because you are filled

41:08.964 --> 41:11.839
with the Lord's love.
Yes. Feel it.

41:11.923 --> 41:14.714
♪ (CHOIR SINGING) ♪

41:21.422 --> 41:23.339
Well, it's certainly not
without compensation.

41:23.422 --> 41:25.005
You're gonna have every
newspaper in the country

41:25.089 --> 41:26.381
printing your firm's name.

41:26.464 --> 41:28.923
You can't pay
for the kind of advertising

41:29.005 --> 41:30.172
the Dodson case will...

41:30.255 --> 41:32.381
-DILLON: Miss Street!
-I'm on the phone!

41:33.673 --> 41:35.714
Well, no one
would expect you to.

41:35.798 --> 41:38.673
-DILLON: I need you in here!
-Just a second!

41:41.881 --> 41:43.714
Can you--
Can you think of anyone else

41:43.798 --> 41:45.839
who might consider-- Hello?

41:47.005 --> 41:48.547
DILLON: Miss Street!

41:56.756 --> 41:58.339
Did you need something,
Mr. Dillon?

41:58.422 --> 42:00.047
Miss Street, these case files,

42:00.130 --> 42:02.339
is-- is this-- is this
everything you had?

42:02.422 --> 42:04.005
As far as I know, Mr. Dillon.

42:04.089 --> 42:06.047
DILLON: Because there isn't
a whole lot here,

42:06.130 --> 42:07.756
aside from some photographs
and a stack

42:07.839 --> 42:09.255
of illegible notes
from Mr. Mason.

42:09.339 --> 42:11.381
DELLA: Well, I think you'll find
some motions in there as well.

42:11.464 --> 42:13.673
Yeah. You mentioned yesterday,
you said something

42:13.756 --> 42:15.172
about new evidence?

42:15.255 --> 42:17.005
Oh. Yes.

42:17.089 --> 42:19.339
Right. So where is it?

42:19.422 --> 42:21.923
Gee, Mr. Dillon,
if it's not there...

42:22.005 --> 42:24.005
It's not.

42:24.089 --> 42:26.673
Well, I suppose I could dash
by Mr. Jonathan's tonight

42:26.756 --> 42:28.506
and see
if he took anything home.

42:28.589 --> 42:31.422
DILLON: That'd be wonderful.
Thank you.

42:31.506 --> 42:33.839
Miss Street, is there a trick
to using these phones?

42:33.923 --> 42:35.339
DELLA: It's a phone, Mr. Dillon.

42:35.422 --> 42:37.047
You pick it up
and tell the operator

42:37.130 --> 42:38.547
what number you'd like to call.

42:38.631 --> 42:40.964
Right. Bit more complicated
than what we have

42:41.047 --> 42:42.798
at the public defenders--
Hello, operator?

42:42.881 --> 42:45.297
Yes.
Uh, DA's office, please.

42:48.964 --> 42:54.005
♪ (JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

43:04.130 --> 43:05.673
MAYNARD BARNES (ON PHONE):
Nothing in the files?

43:05.756 --> 43:07.047
DILLON (ON PHONE):
Well, I'm still looking

43:07.130 --> 43:08.923
through the notes
from the detective.

43:09.005 --> 43:11.881
A real unsavory character
with some shoddy penmanship.

43:12.005 --> 43:13.756
BARNES: Bring me
whatever notes he left tomorrow.

43:13.839 --> 43:15.881
DILLON:
Say your office, noon?

43:15.964 --> 43:17.089
BARNES:
Not my fucking office.

43:17.172 --> 43:18.422
The place we met the other time.

43:18.506 --> 43:20.172
DILLON:
Of course. Sorry.

43:26.923 --> 43:30.172
Stashing evidence,
hidden secrets.

43:30.255 --> 43:32.798
This is like when I covered
Myrna in The Black Watch.

43:32.881 --> 43:35.964
"It is sweeter to be
a woman to one man

43:36.047 --> 43:38.339
than goddess to thousands."

43:40.881 --> 43:42.422
I could help, you know?

43:42.506 --> 43:43.756
You're a klutz.

43:43.839 --> 43:46.422
And Myrna
would never forgive me.

43:46.506 --> 43:47.839
Three more trips.

43:47.923 --> 43:50.130
HAZEL PRYSTOCK: Should I
be worried about you?

43:50.214 --> 43:52.464
I mean,
just how illegal is this?

43:54.214 --> 43:57.422
Well, the way I see it,

43:57.506 --> 44:01.005
there's what's legal
and there's what's right.

44:12.631 --> 44:15.005
EMILY: The officers said
that I'm supposed to be indoors

44:15.089 --> 44:16.464
by nighttime.

44:16.547 --> 44:19.005
I don't see any officers
around, do you?

44:21.881 --> 44:27.547
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

44:50.089 --> 44:52.923
(SOBBING)

45:25.381 --> 45:26.464
Sister Alice?

45:29.047 --> 45:32.422
Will you have to dig up
Charlie when you do it?

45:37.673 --> 45:38.756
DIANNE (ON PHONE):
Message exchange.

45:38.839 --> 45:40.047
-MASON: It's Mason.
-DIANNE: He lives.

45:40.130 --> 45:41.756
-MASON: What do you got for me?
-DIANNE: A lot.

45:41.839 --> 45:43.047
Just give me today's.

45:43.130 --> 45:44.964
DIANNE: Mr. Strickland.
Miss Street. Miss Street again.

45:45.047 --> 45:46.297
Miss Street a third time.

45:46.381 --> 45:47.381
She leave a message?

45:47.464 --> 45:49.673
DIANNE: She says
the court has appointed--

45:53.547 --> 45:54.756
(LAUGHS)

45:54.839 --> 45:56.047
DILLON: What's funny?

45:56.130 --> 45:59.339
Oh, you are.
Endlessly, Frank.

45:59.422 --> 46:00.631
May I ask what you're doing?

46:00.714 --> 46:03.589
Well, you are really making
yourself comfortable here,

46:03.673 --> 46:04.714
aren't you?

46:04.798 --> 46:07.673
It's paid through the end
of the month, so...

46:07.756 --> 46:11.756
A good man sat behind this desk.
A good man.

46:11.839 --> 46:13.506
You are not him.

46:17.714 --> 46:19.506
Glass houses, Mr. Mason.

46:19.589 --> 46:21.589
And I'm the lawyer
in charge here.

46:21.673 --> 46:24.047
These reports on the Dodson case
are all incomplete,

46:24.130 --> 46:25.923
and I need you
to decipher your notes.

46:26.005 --> 46:28.130
MASON: I know.
My penmanship's a fright.

46:28.214 --> 46:32.047
Oh! Tolstoy.
"If you want to be happy, be."

46:33.506 --> 46:35.798
What do you want
with my notes, Frank?

46:35.881 --> 46:37.255
-Is that alcohol?
-MASON: Mm-hmm.

46:37.339 --> 46:38.422
That's illegal.

46:38.506 --> 46:39.923
MASON: Only the production,
transport, and sale.

46:40.005 --> 46:42.297
The part where I pour it down
my throat is not only comforting

46:42.381 --> 46:45.547
given your presence here,
but a-okay with Johnny Law.

46:45.631 --> 46:49.756
As an officer of the court,
I must insist.

46:50.214 --> 46:52.673
Mm-hmm. Hmm.

46:55.130 --> 46:56.172
Damn it.

46:56.964 --> 46:59.047
You ever read a book, Frank?

47:00.673 --> 47:03.839
I tell my son
it's important to learn.

47:05.172 --> 47:06.297
Goddammit, Mason.

47:06.381 --> 47:07.756
To go to school.

47:07.839 --> 47:12.130
To get on in life
with understanding, compassion.

47:12.214 --> 47:16.506
What chance does he have, Frank?
What chance does any of us have?

47:16.589 --> 47:17.798
Someone call the police!

47:17.881 --> 47:19.547
What if I just popped
your head, Frank,

47:19.631 --> 47:22.047
like a shiny pussball
full of rot?

47:22.130 --> 47:25.881
Just squeeze and squeeze,
until... (POPS)

47:29.255 --> 47:32.381
I have friends downtown, Mason!
Downtown!

47:32.464 --> 47:33.714
(BLOWS RASPBERRY)

47:35.673 --> 47:38.255
MASON: Fair to assume
that Barnes knows everything

47:38.339 --> 47:41.422
-we do at this point?
-Not everything.

47:41.506 --> 47:44.047
I gave Frank your notes,
which are illegible

47:44.130 --> 47:46.589
and a bunch of stuff
we already filed.

47:46.673 --> 47:48.214
Stashed the rest of it here.

47:48.297 --> 47:50.339
MASON: Brilliant,
but what does it matter?

47:50.422 --> 47:52.464
The court will make sure
that Frank gets everything

47:52.547 --> 47:54.756
at some point, then the DA
gets it the day later.

47:56.339 --> 48:01.089
-What is the DA's case so far?
-Love letters and bias.

48:01.673 --> 48:02.839
MASON: Exactly.

48:02.923 --> 48:06.964
I mean, do they got
bloodied baby clothes? No.

48:07.047 --> 48:08.547
Do they got an operator
listening in

48:08.631 --> 48:10.631
as George and Emily
plot their escape?

48:10.714 --> 48:11.673
No.

48:11.756 --> 48:13.047
MASON: Do they got her
vacationing in Milwaukee

48:13.130 --> 48:15.047
-where the kidnappers come from?
-I'm gonna venture no.

48:15.130 --> 48:16.381
MASON: I'm gonna guarantee a no.

48:16.464 --> 48:18.297
So Barnes is gonna load the jury
with twelve teetotalling,

48:18.381 --> 48:20.881
high-Christian assholes
and hammer away on Emily

48:20.964 --> 48:23.589
for being a cheat and take every
opportunity to show

48:23.673 --> 48:25.714
photographs of Charlie
on the morgue table.

48:25.798 --> 48:26.756
You know why?

48:26.839 --> 48:30.339
'Cause they don't have a shred,
a fucking sliver

48:30.422 --> 48:32.089
of physical evidence.

48:32.172 --> 48:36.589
This standard of behavior
of what? Of--

48:37.297 --> 48:38.714
-Of--
-Personal ethics?

48:38.798 --> 48:41.172
Yes! Because if you walk
out of that door

48:41.255 --> 48:43.422
and think for one second
that you're entering

48:43.506 --> 48:46.464
into a nation of laws,
you are a complete

48:46.547 --> 48:47.714
fucking idiot.

48:47.798 --> 48:49.464
I'm not even talking about
the monster that stitched

48:49.547 --> 48:51.464
those eye sockets open.
He just wanted the cash.

48:51.547 --> 48:53.714
I'm talking about the cops
who are, at best,

48:53.798 --> 48:55.172
covering their asses.

48:55.255 --> 48:56.798
And that--
and that fucking Matthew

48:56.881 --> 48:58.130
who said, "Fuck you, Emily."

48:58.214 --> 48:59.756
I'm just gonna go with a dad
that denied me.

48:59.839 --> 49:01.339
And Barnes here,
you know this is all he's got.

49:01.422 --> 49:02.923
Unless the mayor's
talked to him and said,

49:03.005 --> 49:04.506
"No. No. This is how
we make the sausage.

49:04.589 --> 49:06.756
This is how we keep the order."

49:06.839 --> 49:08.589
-You want coffee?
-I've got coffee.

49:08.673 --> 49:10.422
-DELLA: That's whiskey.
-MASON: Oh, yes, it is.

49:10.506 --> 49:12.130
You know what?
Maybe there is a God.

49:12.214 --> 49:15.047
Maybe there is a God
with a big white stupid beard

49:15.130 --> 49:16.422
that says
"This is how it's gonna be."

49:16.506 --> 49:20.881
But, ladies and gentlemen
of the jury, we have a system

49:20.964 --> 49:23.839
that says you 12 fuckers
can make things right.

49:23.923 --> 49:26.381
Emily Dodson doesn't have to eat
the sins of Los Angeles.

49:26.464 --> 49:28.422
She doesn't have to die
for us sinners.

49:28.506 --> 49:30.255
But they're not gonna do that,
'cause they were raised

49:30.339 --> 49:32.798
in the same city as the rest
of these gutless

49:32.881 --> 49:35.881
fucking attorneys
who won't take this on.

49:36.839 --> 49:37.964
Is that my Underwood?

49:38.047 --> 49:40.005
DELLA: Sorry, June.
Emergency.

49:40.089 --> 49:43.130
There are people upstairs
trying to sleep.

49:43.214 --> 49:46.714
Perry, would you be kind enough
to offer Miss Pitlick a drink?

49:46.798 --> 49:48.422
Oh, well, I...

49:48.923 --> 49:50.172
I'd be honored.

49:52.089 --> 49:54.381
Occasionally, I, uh...

49:58.464 --> 50:01.798
-Purely for medicinal purposes.
-Oh, me too.

50:01.881 --> 50:05.339
-What, uh, what's the emergency?
-Finding our lawyer.

50:25.589 --> 50:27.839
Now, we just got to get him
in front of Emily

50:27.923 --> 50:29.589
before Dillon gets to her.

50:30.923 --> 50:32.589
No fucking way.

50:33.339 --> 50:34.964
George didn't kill himself?

50:36.172 --> 50:37.381
MASON: No.

50:38.506 --> 50:40.297
Does that mean that
George is innocent?

50:41.506 --> 50:42.589
No.

50:42.673 --> 50:45.881
But what it does mean, Emily,
is that you need

50:45.964 --> 50:48.422
new representation,
and you need it now.

50:48.506 --> 50:50.839
And you want her
to engage Mr. Mason?

50:50.964 --> 50:53.589
He's done all the significant
work on this case.

50:53.673 --> 50:56.381
He knows more about it
than anyone in this city.

50:56.464 --> 50:59.381
And he's committed
to making sure the truth

50:59.464 --> 51:02.589
comes out in court
and that your name

51:02.673 --> 51:04.881
and reputation are restored.

51:04.964 --> 51:06.923
-But he's not a lawyer.
-DELLA: Actually...

51:08.381 --> 51:10.839
Mr. Mason has been
under an apprenticeship

51:10.923 --> 51:14.089
with Mr. Jonathan for the
past two-and-a-half years.

51:14.172 --> 51:16.214
There's a bar examination
in two weeks,

51:16.297 --> 51:18.881
which will certify him
with plenty of time

51:18.964 --> 51:20.839
before our trial
is set to begin.

51:26.381 --> 51:29.673
You're being railroaded, Emily,
and it's wrong.

51:29.756 --> 51:31.005
But I can help you.

51:31.089 --> 51:34.673
We can see that you mean
what you say, Mr. Mason,

51:34.756 --> 51:37.422
but it's hard to believe
that you're the right person

51:37.506 --> 51:38.923
for the job.

51:39.005 --> 51:41.547
MASON: Well, I'm the
only person for this job

51:41.631 --> 51:42.798
because we've called everyone.

51:42.881 --> 51:46.506
And you can too.
But no one wants this case.

51:46.589 --> 51:48.005
I'm all you got.

51:48.089 --> 51:51.130
But I will prove
your innocence, Emily.

51:51.214 --> 51:53.673
And I will find
Charlie's killer.

51:53.756 --> 51:56.047
The choice here
is Mrs. Dodson's.

52:00.547 --> 52:01.547
Emily?

52:10.005 --> 52:13.339
I want you to
represent me, Mr. Mason.

52:14.172 --> 52:16.047
You won't regret this.

52:18.172 --> 52:19.589
MASON: What have we done, Della?

52:19.673 --> 52:21.798
We gave our client
a fighting chance.

52:21.881 --> 52:24.631
Client? I have a client?
How the fuck do I have a client?

52:24.714 --> 52:27.172
-What do I know about the law?
-DELLA: More than you think.

52:27.255 --> 52:29.798
-Or nothing.
-Somewhere in the middle.

52:29.881 --> 52:31.547
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

52:34.381 --> 52:35.631
Wh-- Where are you going?

52:35.714 --> 52:37.589
This is our hour
of great regret.

52:38.214 --> 52:40.214
You have an appointment.

52:48.089 --> 52:50.339
I hear you need
some legal advice.

52:50.881 --> 52:51.964
I don't know you.

52:52.047 --> 52:54.089
That's good,
'cause I'm not here.

52:56.339 --> 52:59.964
Oh, hot tea.
Um... slice of lemon.

53:02.756 --> 53:05.673
The suits in City Hall
are scared of something

53:05.756 --> 53:07.339
about the Dodson case.

53:07.422 --> 53:10.714
You probably know more
about why that is than I do.

53:10.798 --> 53:14.172
Right. So what do you have
that I don't?

53:14.255 --> 53:16.506
A law degree from Yale,

53:16.589 --> 53:19.464
22 years of trial experience,
and an office

53:19.547 --> 53:22.297
one floor below Maynard Barnes.

53:22.673 --> 53:23.631
That it?

53:23.714 --> 53:27.047
(LAUGHS)
Della said you were a hard-ass.

53:27.130 --> 53:28.964
Just a little guarded
about tea drinkers

53:29.047 --> 53:31.589
peddling free legal advice.

53:33.673 --> 53:37.464
The bar exam has not changed
since 1923.

53:39.506 --> 53:40.839
Do you have something
to write on

53:40.923 --> 53:42.881
or do you expect
to remember the whole thing?

53:42.964 --> 53:44.798
Why don't we start
with who you are.

53:44.881 --> 53:47.547
-Hamilton Burger.
-I've heard of that name.

53:47.631 --> 53:50.798
Deputy District Attorney
Hamilton Burger.

53:51.839 --> 53:56.297
Oh, you're gunning
for Barnes' job.

53:57.839 --> 53:58.923
Miss?

54:00.964 --> 54:02.923
You forgot
my slice of lemon.

54:05.631 --> 54:09.798
John operated a successful
fishing shop.

54:09.881 --> 54:13.547
He needed a new bait cooler,
which had to be in place

54:13.631 --> 54:16.881
by May 1
for the opening day of,

54:16.964 --> 54:17.923
you guessed it,

54:18.005 --> 54:21.297
the fishing season.
Write this down.

54:21.381 --> 54:27.506
On, uh, February 1, John entered
into a valid written contract...

54:27.589 --> 54:29.673
LAWYERS: "I do solemnly swear

54:29.756 --> 54:33.214
I will support the Constitution
of the United States

54:33.297 --> 54:37.089
and the Constitution
of the State of California.

54:37.172 --> 54:40.547
I will employ such means only
as are consistent

54:40.631 --> 54:42.756
with truth and honor.

54:42.839 --> 54:46.589
I will maintain the confidence
and preserve inviolate

54:46.673 --> 54:48.881
the secrets of my client.

54:48.964 --> 54:52.130
I will abstain from all
offensive personality

54:52.214 --> 54:55.130
unless required
by the justice of the cause

54:55.214 --> 54:56.964
with which I am charged.

54:57.047 --> 55:01.631
I will never reject the cause of
the defenseless or oppressed."

55:01.714 --> 55:03.381
So help me God.

55:04.089 --> 55:05.839
"So help me God."

57:09.881 --> 57:13.464
MAYNARD BARNES:
A trial is society's way
of finding the truth.

57:15.756 --> 57:18.839
If I make a mistake...
someone dies.

57:19.172 --> 57:20.422
Then don't make a mistake.

